    "description": "Alkem Laboratories has an exciting opening for a Surgeon at our Hyderabad office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Alkem Laboratories:\nAlkem Laboratories is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Hyderabad, Telangana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Alkem Laboratories!",
